  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Suppress installation of unnecessary files:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed "s/ install-data-local//" -i Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-data-local//" -i doc/Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-data-local//" -i doc/examples/Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-dist_docsDATA//" -i python/Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-dist_exampleDATA//" -i python/tests/Makefile.in
sed "s/ install-dist_devhelpDATA//" -i doc/devhelp/Makefile.in</userinput></screen>

    <para>
       Apply two upstream fixes, which correct bugs in
       <command>xmlcatalog</command> and in the entity substitution
       mechanism:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed \
  -e /xmlInitializeCatalog/d \
  -e 's/((ent->checked =.*&amp;&amp;/(((ent->checked == 0) ||\
          ((ent->children == NULL) \&amp;\&amp; (ctxt->options \&amp; XML_PARSE_NOENT))) \&amp;\&amp;/' \
  -i parser.c</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Prepare the package for compilation:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --disable-static \
            --with-python=/usr/bin/python3 \
            --with-history</userinput></screen>
    <para>
      Compile the package:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install the package:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make -j1 install
rm -v /usr/lib/libxml2.la</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--with-python=/usr/bin/python3</parameter>: This switch
        enables building the Python module.
      </para>

      <para>
        <parameter>--with-history</parameter>: This switch enables Readline
        support when running <command>xmlcatalog</command> or
        <command>xmllint</command> in shell mode.
      </para>

    </sect3>

